  "description": "EDK (Embedded Development Kit) is a project to enable UEFI support for Virtual Machines. This package contains a sample 64-bit UEFI firmware for QEMU and KVM.   \n\nSecurity Fix(es):  \n\n  * openssl: Out-of-bounds read \u0026 write in RFC 3211 KEK Unwrap (CVE-2025-9230)\n\n\nBug Fix(es) and Enhancement(s):  \n\n  * [FJ8.10 Bug] How to Update Secure Boot Certificates with Microsoft 2023 in KVM Guests (JIRA:AlmaLinux-151949)\n\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n",
